), apex sinuous in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–20" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 13 - 20. Brachiacantha hexaspina sp. nov. male 13 Dorsal view 14 Abdomen 15 Tegmen 16 Tegmen lateral view 17 Penis 18 Penis apex 19 Paramere 20 Penis guide. Scale bar: 1 mm, except 15 - 20 0.5 mm" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.56927.figures13-20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520869" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">16</figureCitation>
); parameres wide basally, narrowed to apex, apex rounded, setae rising from the apex border (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–20" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 13 - 20. Brachiacantha hexaspina sp. nov. male 13 Dorsal view 14 Abdomen 15 Tegmen 16 Tegmen lateral view 17 Penis 18 Penis apex 19 Paramere 20 Penis guide. Scale bar: 1 mm, except 15 - 20 0.5 mm" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.56927.figures13-20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520869" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–20" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 13 - 20. Brachiacantha hexaspina sp. nov. male 13 Dorsal view 14 Abdomen 15 Tegmen 16 Tegmen lateral view 17 Penis 18 Penis apex 19 Paramere 20 Penis guide. Scale bar: 1 mm, except 15 - 20 0.5 mm" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.56927.figures13-20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520869" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">19</figureCitation>
); penis curved in basal 
<normalizedToken originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
