<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">hexa</emphasis>
(= six) and Latin 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">spine</emphasis>
(= thorn), referring to the six teeth of the tibiae, long and curved like rose thorns.
